The Chronicle Thupeyo Muleya,Â Beitbridge Bureau Criminal activities have resurfaced at the Alfred Beit bridge (Old Limpopo Bridge) where touts, thieves, conmen, wheeler dealers, vendors are roaming freely under the watchful eyes of security agents. Government declared the border post a security zone in 2004. The bridge is manned by police and members of the army from both Zimbabwe and South Africa. Touts soliciting for smugglers or illegal immigrants and vendors selling food items and water have become a common feature on the bridge.